thread.title: Chinese FDI lifts in September
thread.title_full: Chinese FDI lifts in September | Business Spectator

author: Dow Jones newswires
title: Chinese FDI lifts in September
text:
China's foreign direct investment rose 7.1 per cent from a year earlier in September, the Ministry of Commerce said in a statement on Monday.
The world's second-largest economy attracted $US9.56 billion in FDI the previous month, the ministry said.
In the January-to-September period, China's FDI increased 9 per cent year-over-year to $US94.9 billion, according to the official data.
